- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is likely because the paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze the content of legislative speeches in the European Parliament. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is likely because the paper analyzes political interactions in the European Parliament, which can be seen as a social network of MEPs. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is likely because the paper uses a new method for dynamic topic modeling, which can be applied to large corpora of text data, such as the corpus of legislative speeches in the EP plenary. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely because the paper uses matrix factorization techniques for topic modeling, which are a type of machine learning method. 
- cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) is less likely, but still possible, because the paper analyzes the content of speeches made in the EP plenary, which can be seen as a form of audio data.
